OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FParliament drug use claims 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fto be raised with police   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fthis week                  
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, House of Commons Speaker Sir Lindsay   
OL,6, Hoyle has promised to raise allegations
OL,7, of drug use in Parliament with the     
OL,8, Metropolitan Police this week.         
OL,10,FHe described a report in the Sunday    
OL,11,FTimes that traces of cocaine had been  
OL,12,Ffound in several lavatory areas as     
OL,13,F"deeply concerning".                   
OL,15,FSir Lindsay told the BBC that those who
OL,16,F"flout the law" should face punishment.
OL,18,FHis decision comes as the government is
OL,19,Fexpected on Monday to pledge #700m over
OL,20,Fthree years to tackle problem drug use.
